    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-14T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="551"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/200: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-14T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 14, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>207. <persName corresp="#p_BEGB1">Blanche</persName> has resumed the Provisional
                    Presidency and has appointed <persName corresp="#p_LCP1">Lagos</persName>
                    Minister of War. The infantry took the military aviation field but <persName
                        corresp="#p_MRR1">Merino</persName> and most of his aeroplanes had gone to a
                    commercial landing field north of Santiago. Guns are mounted in the Moneda and
                    neighboring buildings. A state of expectancy prevails.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
